<p>Thom is Artistic Director of Charing Cross Theatre.</p>

<p>Theatre includes: the UK première of <i>Harold And Maude</i>, Andrew Lloyd Webber’s <i>The Woman In White</i>, <i>Death Takes A Holiday</i>, <i>Ragtime</i>, <i>The Mikado</i> (Charing Cross Theatre); <i>The Pajama Game</i> (Tokyo & Osaka, Japan); <i>Angela’s Ashes The Musical</i> (Belfast & Dublin); <i>Allegro, Grey Gardens, Mack & Mabel, Victor/Victoria, Parade</i> (Southwark Playhouse); <i>Titanic</i> (UK and Ireland tour; Charing Cross Theatre; Princess Of Wales, Toronto; Tokyo & Osaka, Japan; Southwark Playhouse - longlisted, Evening Standard Theatre Award for Best Musical 2013; winner, Broadway World UK Award for Best Fringe/Regional Musical 2013, WhatsOnStage Award for Best Off West End Production and 4 Off West End Awards including Best Musical Production); <i>Grand Hotel</i> (Tokyo, Japan; Southwark Playhouse); <i>The Smallest Show On Earth</i>, which he also co-wrote (Mercury Theatre, Colchester & UK tour); <i>Peter Pan</i> (US tour); <i>The Grand Tour, Me And Juliet</i> (Finborough Theatre); <i>Noël And Gertie</i> (Cockpit Theatre); Rodgers and Hammerstein’s <i>State Fair</i> (Finborough Theatre & Trafalgar Studios); <i>Hobson’s Choice</i> (Broadway Theatre, Catford); <i>I Sing, Annie Get Your Gun, The Pajama Game</i>, all-male adaptations of <i>HMS Pinafore</i> and <i>The Mikado</i> (Union Theatre).</p>

<p><a href="http://www.thomsoutherland.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.thomsoutherland.co.uk</a></p>

